  "summary": "Malicious code in @klapp-about/routes (npm)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: amazon-inspector (3a89d8d92c1d5303d17c64a14353dfd86d738d620129a830af3684b6ab2e2167)\nOn `npm install`, the package's preinstall hook (`node index.js || true`) automatically runs index.js, which collects host identifiers (os.hostname(), os.userInfo().username, __dirname, process.cwd()) and exfiltrates them via two channels: a hex-encoded subdomain DNS lookup against `*.d8jbmnsqcfu78dfs8vdg34ohqhirb4pbg.oast.live` (interactsh-style OAST responder) and an HTTP POST of the JSON payload to bare IP `172.201.213.59:9090/c`. Errors are suppressed (`|| true`) so the beacon stays silent and install never fails. The fetch fires unconditionally before any user code runs and has no relation to any documented package functionality.\n",
